I have to say..if anyone is the head of our household, it would be me! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :lol --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/laugh.gif ALT=":lol"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   I do all the banking, bill paying etc. DH doesn't have a clue how much money we have!  I am the &quot;traditional&quot; wife as well..I stay at home with the kids (although DH is at home all the time as well)..I do all the housework, cooking, cleaning etc...but I also know that my husband has the utmost respect for me as an equal...all the important descions are made together, as a partnership (which is what I believe marriage is)..if we can't agree to begin with, then we will talk it through.  I don't think I could live with a man who didn't respect me as an equal.<br>
<br>
I also wanted to comment about the &quot;kids out of wedlock&quot; thing...I can't remember who said it, but someone said something along the lines of &quot;everyone would agree that a child is better off being raised by two loving parents than by one&quot;.  While I certainly agree with that statement, I don't think you need to be married to be committed, loving, etc.  The only reason I got married was because my mum felt so strongly about kids being born within marriage (no real reasoning, as she isn't even religious..just a &quot;hang up&quot; she has)..and I wanted my children to have the same name as their dad (less confusion)...but as far as the actual marriage, it is nothing more than a piece of paper to me.  My feelings for my husband didn't change once I married him, I felt exactly the same on the day after my wedding, as I had the day before - if it hadn't been for my mums views, I would probably have just changed my name by deedpoll and left it at that! <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
