<br>
Scenario...<br>
Two parents are discussing discipline for their child.  The child has broken something that belonged to the father.  Had no monetary value but meant something to the father.  The father wants to spank the child and the mother wants to give the child time out.  Now these two parents have an equal relationship, both have an equal say in EVERY thing in their house.  How do you discipline the child?  Would you do both? Equal punishment so that both opinions are respected?  Or would you do nothing, both opinions respected?  (Also keep in mind the roles can be reversed, the mother's thing got broken or whatever, since this is an equal situation.)<br>
<br>
Scenario...<br>
A married couple go car shopping.  The wife wants to get a minivan, no kids yet but planning on a family.  The husband wants a two seater sports car, the kids won't be for two or three years, plenty of time to trade it in later for the minivan.  How do you respect both people, give equal consideration to each persons wants/needs?  Buy both cars, or buy none?<br>
<br>
I know that I am not thinking these through fully enough, but they just popped into my head.  I am submissive to my husband and sometimes I get upset with the decisions he makes, and I don't NOT make decisions.  I just discuss things with him first.  I would assume all of the people here have to submit in some way or another to there spouse.  It isn't like submissive people grovel or beg to their spouses.  There is still respect involved in the marriage.  If there isn't respect by both parties then some one is being abused and that is not what the submission in my house is like.  My husband likes the fact that I think for myself and I compliment him in many ways with the fact that I am not some wet noodle.  But he is the head of my house and I respect him.  <br>
<br>
Anyway, that is it for now, I think this is my longest post ever.<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
