<br>
When my wife and I bought our cars we laid out the budget and decided what we could afford.  We ran thru consumer reports and buyer guides and decided what we needed.  We then went out and shopped around some (I say some because a long time friend of mine manages a dealership so we always end up getting the best deal from him) and made our purchase.  When I bought my car she played devils advocate for me as the voice of reason, when she bought her car I played devils advocate for her as the voice of reason.  The part that impacts us both (money) we worked out together.  The parts that impacted us individually more (what car wed be stuck in) the individual took the lead on.  <br>
<br>
When it comes to discipline of our kids, we dont spank unless their life is in jeopardy (ex: fork in an outlet) and that has been one time, between 2 kids, ever.  If you communicate with people effectively, yes even children, then you dont need to resort to violence and battery to get your way.  I was raised in a spanking household.  I came into my relationship expecting to be spanking my kids.  I was shown the error of my ways and have since not spanked my kids.  My wife did the research, she showed me her info, she persuasively argued her case and I quite happily abide by her recommendation because it was right all on its own, irrespective of which of us presented it.  Facts win out.  Violence is the last resort if the ignorant.<br>
<br>
Heather, despite your kind words about the worth of my question, I am still left wondering, if the OT law was abolished, and the NT law is all we need, and as your article points out and CEREMONIAL law is worthless, how does this reconcile with the first 3 commandments since they are all ceremonial as well?  The answer that I think I know is that you selectively apply the bible to your life.  I think that following the bible strictly is impossible in this day and age and that while you apply it more rigidly than most, you still fall short of the mark.  I further call you out on the I havent studied this out myself hooey because if your immortal soul is in jeopardy, you damn well better study it out or you are a hypocrite and a liar before god.  If he can curse a fig tree to wither and die, never to bear fruit again when it wasnt even in SEASON, how will he take your decision to disregard whole sections of his laws?  Nope, you are not a true christian and you certainly arent saved. <br>
<br>
See you in hell.<br>
